  "description": "WTP Upgrade Phase I",
  "enriched_description": "GUC's largest-ever water infrastructure investment, expanding capacity from 22.5 MGD to 32 MGD (42% increase) to serve regional growth through 2035. Secured $29M EPA WIFIA loan - federal recognition of Greenville as 'one of the fastest growing municipal regions in North Carolina.' Uses advanced superpulsator technology combining rapid mix, flocculation, and sedimentation in a single tank. Original 1983 plant (12 MGD) \u2192 2002 expansion (22.5 MGD) \u2192 now 32 MGD. Serves 131,161+ population. Critical capacity for recruiting industrial users like Boviet ($400M) and NIPRO ($398M). Project completed and operational - watch for Phase II planning as demand grows.",
